Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @Carrot{3}(trimmed, halved lengthways and chopped into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Sprinkle the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet} over both sides of the chicken breasts and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken breasts flat in the pan. Fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

While the chicken fries, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and @Chermoula Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Fry for ~{30%seconds}, then add the @Couscous{120%grams} and stir until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Couscous{200%ml}. Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Pop a lid on the pan and leave to the side, off the heat, for ~{8-10%minutes}, or until ready to serve.

Once the chicken is cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

Drizzle over the @Honey{1/2%tbsp} (see pantry for amount) and add a knob of @?butter{knob} if you have any.

Turn the chicken so it is nicely glazed. Set aside to rest for a few mins.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Stir through the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%grams} and roasted carrots.

Once rested, transfer the chicken to a board and slice widthways into 1cm slices (keep any remaining juices from the chicken pan).

Share the couscous and carrots between your #bowls{} and top with the herby chicken.

Spoon any remaining juices from the pan over the chicken, then drizzle the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{75%grams} over everything.

Serve the @Wild Rocket{20%grams} alongside, drizzled with a little @olive oil{drizzle}.

Enjoy!